[{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"text":"Session Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Project: Behind paywall | Date: 2026-03-25 | Messages: 148"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"text":"Conversation Excerpt"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🧑 You"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"I completely understand. As a non-developer, your goal is to act as the product manager—you want to hand a blueprint to your AI assistant (Cursor or Claude Code) and have it do all the heavy lifting, from creating the folders to writing the code and setting up the database, without stopping to ask you technical questions.\nTo achieve your goal of persistence across multiple computers and browsers, a purely local application won’t work. The AI needs to build a modern web application connected to a free cloud database (like Supabase) so your sessions, tokens, and saved content follow you everywhere.\nBelow is the Master Copy-Paste Prompt. Copy everything inside the blockquote below and paste it directly into Cursor or Claude Code. It contains the granular, step-by-step instructions the AI need"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Acknowledged. I've read all instructions carefully."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Before I begin Phase 1, let me check the current working directory state, then I'll need just two pieces of information from you."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Directory is empty — ready for a clean build."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"**Before I execute Phase 1-3 autonomously, I need these two values from you in one batch:**"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"1. **Supabase Project URL** — looks like: `https://xxxxxxxxxxxxxx.supabase.co`\n2. **Supabase Anon (Public) Key** — a long JWT string starting with `eyJ...`"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🧑 You"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"__https://supabase.insightprofit.live__\nJWT_SECRET=kmuZC5ZHoc3JezmKDDFmp4et+eOppz//g6ZCk4UOzJg=\nANON_KEY=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJyb2xlIjoiYW5vbiIsImlzcyI6InN1cGFiYXNlIiwiaWF0IjoxNzY2ODcxMjQ0LCJleHAiOjIwODIyMzEyNDR9.qtJF1pWQQr-SGHVYLv0wP4hMiamqfjrNsfsnBm-c2hI\nSERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJyb2xlIjoic2VydmljZV9yb2xlIiwiaXNzIjoic3VwYWJhc2UiLCJpYXQiOjE3NjY4NzEyNDQsImV4cCI6MjA4MjIzMTI0NH0._MTLkX32ncAWUnnYkEPLx4L74xllYllJsjgdylfhLaQ\nyou can do it all for me"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n- Self-hosted Supabase (like `supabase.insightprofit.live`) works identically to the cloud version — the Supabase JS client just points to your custom URL instead of `*.supabase.co`\n- The Service Role Key bypasses Row Level Security, so it's used only server-side (API routes) — never exposed to the browser\n- Next.js App Router separates server components (direct DB access) from client components (browser interactivity), which is perfect for this proxy architecture\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Got everything I need. Starting full autonomous build now."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"**Phase 1 — Scaffolding**"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Good, `.gitignore` already covers `.env*`. Let me check what Next.js version this is and read its docs as instructed by AGENTS.md."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"... and 142 more messages in this session."}]}]
